Men are making most of the decisions related to the coronavirus pandemic, a new study says.

An analysis of decision-making and key advisory bodies from 87 countries found that over 85% contain mostly men and only 11% contain predominantly women. https://t.co/bsrQOM6hKp

Matthew Graham and his wife, Jessica, had taken their five kids to meet his brother's new puppy last month when a wildfire destroyed their home and almost everything they owned.

Two weeks later, all seven of them tested positive for Covid-19. https://t.co/YCO8XNSzHa
